<TITLE> Dhaka to seek recession aid: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Apr 15 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh will seek budgetary support from donors to fight the fallouts of the global economic recession, the finance minister said Wednesday. "This assistance will be meant for 2009-10. Several agencies including the World Bank have already been approached," A M A Muhith told a BEI roundtable discussion. Salman Rahman, chairman of Bangladesh Enterprise Institute (BEI), chaired the discussions, attended by the US and UK envoys, BEI president Farooq Sobhan, Beximco Group chairman Sohel Rahman, FBCCI chief Annisul Huq, economist professor Abu Ahmed, Mamtajuddin Ahmed and former ambassador in Geneva Debapriya Bhattacharya. US Ambassador James Moriarty said it would be difficult to predict the duration of the on-going recession and that each country had to prepare for any likely impact. UK high commissioner Stephan Evans said Bangladesh would surely benefit from the global recession package for LDCs announced by the G-20 natio
